      }}>{`Python-based integration`}</a>{`, as the PagerDuty Agent requires a newer version of Python than the version available with CentOS 5.`}</p>
    <p>{`##Verify the Agent is Running
Once you've verified the agent has been successfully installed, you'll want to make sure that it is running. You can check the status by running `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`service pdagent status`}</inlineCode>{`. If the agent isn't running, you can start it with the command `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`service pdagent start`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`##Check the Agent's Logs for Errors
The agent logs activity and errors to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/var/log/pdagent/pdagentd.log`}</inlineCode>{`, which may contain information helpful in troubleshooting problems with the integration.`}</p>
